telepathy, the ability to read and communicate with another's mind. Fallen

a way that represents that thought as our own, when it is not. Hard to 
believe until you think of all the thoughts that seem to come from nowhere. 
For a demon to even be considered to be affiliated with temptation, there 
must be a point of contact. This point of contact must also be in a way we 
do not realize they are present and moving against us. If we knew, we would 
not fall to temptation. There is a point of contact and it is in our minds. 
They have been doing this for quite some time and the less we know about 
their presence, the more they are able to affect our judgments.

this ability..... and so is the priest. This is why a priest almost always

convicted upon our first judgment. The fallen move against the demons to 
maintain their{demon} status as guilty for the second judgment which is 
mentioned in The Bible in Revelation.

attention. These other people may not have demons who have entered, but 
they most likely do have demons paying them attention and can read their 
thoughts thanks to the fallen angels. Depending upon how long these demons

back into the memory of the other that the possessed would appear to be

have been with us our entire lives. Nothing has changed from yesterday, you
